reviews.review_text:
Cool show, tight recording I have bveen weeding thru the GEMS oferings on the Archive and found this little gem. I came for the Shakedown and ended listening to the whole thing. The boys open with a rockin' Shakedown and also play a very nice Althea in the first set. The second set highlights include a very tasty thrice-appearing Playin' and a tender China Doll. THis is an energetic and well-played concert.

Hats off to the tapers who produced a very listenable and sparking recording. Worth it

A Gem for sure! Awesome sound quality on this one. Real nice upbeat show and great mix of tunes. If you're cruising for a nice AUD from the early 80's this one is definitely worth a listen. I'm giving it a 3 instead of a 4 only because I'm forcing myself to be picky about 4's and 5's.
